translated: Years, Ture, district doctor, Gothenburg, born on 11/4/81 in Mularp, Skaraborg. First child of the parson Magnus Å. and Hilda Sofia Cederin. Married on 14 with Hertha Enemark. Children: Sven, born in 15, dentist, Gothenburg; John 17, philosophy student, Gothenburg; Ebba 21, married to civil engineer H. Egnell, Stockholm. Completed matriculation examination in Skara in 00, medical and philosophical studies in Lund in 03, medical candidate in 07, and medical licentiate in Stockholm in 11. Assistant in physiology at Karolinska Institute in 06, various appointments as intern, assistant physician, and deputy physician at different hospitals from 06 to 14. City and hospital doctor in Askersund from 14 to 16, district doctor in Gothenburg from 16 to 20, and again from 26. School doctor in Gothenburg from 16 to 38, doctor at "Mjölkdroppen" (milk droplet) from 16 to 20, assistant doctor at Gibraltar's department for body illness and tuberculosis since 20, and railway doctor at Gothenburg-Särö railway since 25. Studied in Copenhagen and Berlin in 21. Retired in 46.
